Is Testable
=================

Allows test scripts to be added to multiple and different models.

== Resources

Install
 * Copy the is_testable plugin [from the BioCatalogue source]
 
 * Run the following command:
 
   ruby script/generate is_testable_migration
   which will create a migration file with the following contents
 
     class IsTestable < ActiveRecord::Migration
  		def self.up
    		create_table :service_tests do |t|
      			t.string :name ,          :null => false
      			t.string :exec_name ,     :null => false
      			t.string :test_status,    :default =>'UNKNOWN'
      			t.integer :running_status,:default => 0
      			t.binary :test_data,      :null =>false ,:limit => 5.megabyte
      			t.integer :testable_id,   :null => false
      			t.string :testable_type,  :null => false
      			t.text :description,      :null => false
      			t.timestamps
    		end
  		end

  		def self.down
    		drop_table :service_tests
  		end
	end

== Usage
 
 * Make you ActiveRecord model testable.
 
 class Model < ActiveRecord::Base
 	is_testable
 end
 
 * Add a test to a model instance
 
 model = Model.new
 test = ServiceTest.new({<test params>})
 model.service_tests << test
 
 * Each test reference a testable object
 
 model = Model.find(1)
 model.comments.get(0).commtable == model

== Credits

This plugin was heavily influenced by acts as commentable plugin

